description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated therapist to join our acute medicine and surgery team, to further develop your existing experience in this field. With the recent establishment of an acute frailty unit and already established elderly care services, this post will have a particular focus on optimising dementia and elderly care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also have the opportunity to work across specialist clinical areas including respiratory care, major trauma, surgery, gastroenterology and emergency medicine. The post holder will used developed skills including prioritisation and problem solving, with a strong focus on ongoing dynamic learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to be flexible and responsive to the changing service needs involved in cross site working with support from the medical/surgical clinical leads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join an established team, which has strong links with wider multidisciplinary staff and work alongside the medical team, AHP’s and specialist nurses in delivering high quality patient care. We have Videofluoroscopy and FEES clinics which run throughout the week, supporting clinical decision making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Speech and Language therapy service is a big team and is part of Integrated Nutrition and Communication Services which includes the Department of Dietetics and The Nutrition Nurse Team. We are a friendly team with a strong commitment to evidence based practice with regular CPD, appraisal and training opportunities. Established support is available at B7 level and from the Head of Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 24th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
